data.name: label2.ToolTip
data.value:
You can Enable or Disable the Old English keyboard while typing in another application.
For instance, when disabled and typing in Word, press CTRL + P to quickly enable the keyboard to type an Old English Character.
NOTE: Not all Modifier Keys work with every program.

data.name: label3.ToolTip
data.value:
Use the Test Area below to test out the Old English Keyboard before using it on another application. The keyboard will work with applications such as Microsoft Word, Chrome, Fire Fox, Notepad, and other applications where you can enter special characters.
To test if an application will work with the Old English Keyboard, simply open the application in question, enable the Old English Keyboard, Set the Modifier Key to 'None', and press a Key.

data.name: label18.ToolTip
data.value:
The Modifier Key is held down along with one of the keys below to enter the Old English symbol onto a form.
NOTE: Some programs might reject certain Modifier Keys. For instance: Microsoft Word does not work with CTRL or ALT as a Modifier.
